adTSUIQPassword.name: adTSUIQPassword
adTSUIQPassword.description: Sets the Telnet and Vt100 Control Password.

adTSUIQTOD.name: adTSUIQTOD
adTSUIQTOD.description: Sets the Time of Day with format hh:mm.

adTSUIQDate.name: adTSUIQDate
adTSUIQDate.description: Sets the Date with the format MM-DD-YY.

adTSUIQGatewayIpAddress.name: adTSUIQGatewayIpAddress
adTSUIQGatewayIpAddress.description: Sets the Network Gateway IP Address.

adTSUIQTrapManagerIpAddress.name: adTSUIQTrapManagerIpAddress
adTSUIQTrapManagerIpAddress.description: Sets the Trap Manager IP Address.

adTSUIQControPortBaud.name: adTSUIQControPortBaud
adTSUIQControPortBaud.description: Selects the Control Port Baud Rate.

adTSUIQAlarmState.name: adTSUIQAlarmState
adTSUIQAlarmState.description: This bit map variable indicates alarm conditions which are currently set. When an alarm condition occurs, the corresponding event bit is set in this variable. If armed, setting the event will generate an Alarm Trap. The various alarm event bit positions are: 1 = Network physical link up. 2 = Network physical link down. 4 = Network signal state up. 8 = Network signal state down.

adTSUIQArmAlarm.name: adTSUIQArmAlarm
adTSUIQArmAlarm.description: This bit map variable arms or disarms an individual or group of events identified in adFradAlarmState as a source for generation of an Alarm Trap. The various arm event bit positions are : 1 = Network physical link up. 2 = Network physical link down. 4 = Network signal state up. 8 = Network signal state down.

adTSUIQAbortConfig.name: adTSUIQAbortConfig
adTSUIQAbortConfig.description: A Set will cancel current selections and reverts to the last saved configuration.

adTSUIQSaveConfig.name: adTSUIQSaveConfig
adTSUIQSaveConfig.description: A Set will reset the unit and Save the current selections.

adTSUIQNetPortClockSource.name: adTSUIQNetPortClockSource
adTSUIQNetPortClockSource.description: Timing source for the transmit side of the T1 interface.

adTSUIQNetPortLineCode.name: adTSUIQNetPortLineCode
adTSUIQNetPortLineCode.description: Line code for the the T1 interface.

adTSUIQNetRxSensitivity.name: adTSUIQNetRxSensitivity
adTSUIQNetRxSensitivity.description: Selects the gain of receiver for the T1 interface.

adTSUIQNetPortLBO.name: adTSUIQNetPortLBO
adTSUIQNetPortLBO.description: Line build out for the transmit side of the T1 interface.

adTSUIQNetChannelCount.name: adTSUIQNetChannelCount
adTSUIQNetChannelCount.description: Selects the number of active channels for the T1 interface.

adTSUIQNetChannelStart.name: adTSUIQNetChannelStart
adTSUIQNetChannelStart.description: Selects the channel that begins the active channel list for the T1 interface.

adTSUIQNetChannelBandwidth.name: adTSUIQNetChannelBandwidth
adTSUIQNetChannelBandwidth.description: Selects the amount of data in each active channel for the T1 interface.

adTSUIQNetChannelAlignment.name: adTSUIQNetChannelAlignment
adTSUIQNetChannelAlignment.description: Selects the alignment of active channels for the T1 interface.

adTSUIQNetTransmitPRM.name: adTSUIQNetTransmitPRM
adTSUIQNetTransmitPRM.description: Enables performance report generation across the T1 FDL for the T1 interface.

adTSUIQNetPortSignaling.name: adTSUIQNetPortSignaling
adTSUIQNetPortSignaling.description: Signaling type for the frame relay management interface.

adTSUIQNetPortt391.name: adTSUIQNetPortt391
adTSUIQNetPortt391.description: Sets the polling interval in seconds for the frame relay management interface. (Range 5 - 30).

adTSUIQNetPortn391.name: adTSUIQNetPortn391
adTSUIQNetPortn391.description: Sets the interval between full status polls for the frame relay management interface. (Range 1 - 255).

adTSUIQNetPortn392.name: adTSUIQNetPortn392
adTSUIQNetPortn392.description: Sets the error count for the frame relay management interface. (Range 1 - 10).

adTSUIQNetPortn393.name: adTSUIQNetPortn393
adTSUIQNetPortn393.description: Sets the event window for the frame relay management interface. ( Range 1 - 10).

adTSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci1Mode.name: adTSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci1Mode
adTSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci1Mode.description: Sets the mode for the managent DLCI 1. If set for shared, management DLCI 1 is used for customer data and IQ management data. If set for dedicated, management DLCI 1 is used only for IQ management data and is not passed to the attached frame relay DTE device.

adTSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci2Mode.name: adTSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci2Mode
adTSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci2Mode.description: Sets the mode for the managent DLCI 2. If set for shared, management DLCI 2 is used for customer data and IQ management data. If set for dedicated, management DLCI 2 is used only for IQ management data and is not passed to the attached frame relay DTE device.

adTSUIQNetMgmtDlci1.name: adTSUIQNetMgmtDlci1
adTSUIQNetMgmtDlci1.description: Sets the address for management PVC 1. (Range 16 - 1007).

adTSUIQNetMgmtDlci2.name: adTSUIQNetMgmtDlci2
adTSUIQNetMgmtDlci2.description: Sets the address for management PVC 2. (Range 16 - 1007).

adTSUIQNetPortMaxPVCs.name: adTSUIQNetPortMaxPVCs
adTSUIQNetPortMaxPVCs.description: Sets the maxium PVCs supported by the IQ unit. (Range 1 - 100).

adTSUIQNetPortHistIntervals.name: adTSUIQNetPortHistIntervals
adTSUIQNetPortHistIntervals.description: Sets the number of history intervals for storage.

adTSUIQNetPortHistIntervalsAvailable.name: adTSUIQNetPortHistIntervalsAvailable
adTSUIQNetPortHistIntervalsAvailable.description: Returns the number of history intervals allowed based on the maxium number of PVCs selected.

adTSUIQDteCTSOption.name: adTSUIQDteCTSOption
adTSUIQDteCTSOption.description: Selects the Clear to Send (CTS) option.

adTSUIQDteDSROption.name: adTSUIQDteDSROption
adTSUIQDteDSROption.description: Selects the Data Set Ready (DSR) option.

adTSUIQDtePortMgmtDLCI.name: adTSUIQDtePortMgmtDLCI
adTSUIQDtePortMgmtDLCI.description: Selects the DTE Port Management DLCI. (Range 16 - 1007).

adTSUIQDtePortt392.name: adTSUIQDtePortt392
adTSUIQDtePortt392.description: Sets the timeout in seconds between polling intervals. (Range 5 - 30)..

adTSUIQDtePortn392.name: adTSUIQDtePortn392
adTSUIQDtePortn392.description: Sets the number of error events for the frame relay management. (Range 1 - 10)..

adTSUIQDtePortn393.name: adTSUIQDtePortn393
adTSUIQDtePortn393.description: Sets the error window (polling events) for the frame relay management. (Range 1 - 10).

adTSUIQDteTCClockOption.name: adTSUIQDteTCClockOption
adTSUIQDteTCClockOption.description: Sets the phase of the DTE Transmit clock.

adTSUIQDteManagementPvcOption.name: adTSUIQDteManagementPvcOption
adTSUIQDteManagementPvcOption.description: Controls the presence of the DTE management PVC in a full status response to the DTE device.

adTSUIQDteSignalingResponsesOption.name: adTSUIQDteSignalingResponsesOption
adTSUIQDteSignalingResponsesOption.description: Determines how the IQ device will respond to polls from the DTE device during a network failure. If set to always on, the IQ will respond to polls during a network failure. If set to follow network, the IQ will not respond thus emulating a failure to the DTE device. If the IQ is responsible for dial backup, this option should be set to always on.

adTSUIQDteFlowControlOption.name: adTSUIQDteFlowControlOption
adTSUIQDteFlowControlOption.description: Determines how the IQ device will respond to congestion during DBU operation. If set for none, the IQ will drop frames during DBU operation when severe congestion occurs. If set for hardware, the IQ will vary the DTE TC clock in order to control the amount of data offered to the IQ when severe congestion occurs. FECN/BECN mode will set the FECN bit in outbound frames and set BECN bit for inbound frames leaving flow control up to the DTE devices.

adTSUIQPvcCIR.name: adTSUIQPvcCIR
adTSUIQPvcCIR.description: Commited Information Rate for this PVC in Kbps. (Range 0 - 1536).

adTSUIQPvcSequenceOption.name: adTSUIQPvcSequenceOption
adTSUIQPvcSequenceOption.description: Sequence number allows the IQ to detect lost frames across the frame relay service. This option should be disabled for PVCs that do not have IQ on both ends.

adTSUIQPvcDelayPacketOption.name: adTSUIQPvcDelayPacketOption
adTSUIQPvcDelayPacketOption.description: Delay packet option for this PVC allows the IQ to sample round trip delay across the frame relay service. This option should be disabled for PVCs that do not have IQ on both ends.

adTSUIQPvcDBUDLCI.name: adTSUIQPvcDBUDLCI
adTSUIQPvcDBUDLCI.description: Used when this PVC entry is used for dial backup. This value should contain the PVC address as seen on the far end of the PVC.

adTSUIQPvcStatsControl.name: adTSUIQPvcStatsControl
adTSUIQPvcStatsControl.description: Stats Control option determines how the IQ will track statistics for this PVC entry. Auto will allow the IQ to track statistics for a PVC if enough memory is available.

adTSUIQT1State.name: adTSUIQT1State
adTSUIQT1State.description: Current status of the T1 interface

adTSUIQDteControlLeads.name: adTSUIQDteControlLeads
adTSUIQDteControlLeads.description: This bit map integer reflects the current state of the DTE control leads as follows: bit meaning 0 CTS 1 RTS 2 DSR 3 DTR 4 DCD A 1 means the lead is on.

adTSUIQDBUPortType.name: adTSUIQDBUPortType
adTSUIQDBUPortType.description: Returns the DBU card type installed.

adTSUIQLANPortStatus.name: adTSUIQLANPortStatus
adTSUIQLANPortStatus.description: Returns the LAN card type installed.

adTSUIQLEDstatus.name: adTSUIQLEDstatus
adTSUIQLEDstatus.description: This bit map integer reflects TSUIQ front panel LED state as follows: bit meaning 0 TEST 1 ALARM 2 ERROR 3 RD 4 TD 5 CTS 6 RTS

adTSUIQDTESignalingState.name: adTSUIQDTESignalingState
adTSUIQDTESignalingState.description: Current state of the PVC signaling between the TSUIQ and the attached frame relay dte.

adTSUIQNETSignalingState.name: adTSUIQNETSignalingState
adTSUIQNETSignalingState.description: Current state of the PVC signaling between the TSUIQ and the frame relay service.

adTSUIQNETPVCConfigTableSize.name: adTSUIQNETPVCConfigTableSize
adTSUIQNETPVCConfigTableSize.description: Current count of rows in the PVC config table.

adTSUIQDBUState.name: adTSUIQDBUState
adTSUIQDBUState.description: Current state of the DBU interface.

adTSUIQIntT1UnavailableTime.name: adTSUIQIntT1UnavailableTime
adTSUIQIntT1UnavailableTime.description: Amount of time in seconds the T1 port is unavailable due to test or in an inactive state.

adTSUIQIntT1StateChange.name: adTSUIQIntT1StateChange
adTSUIQIntT1StateChange.description: Number of changes in the T1 port state. This includes all normal, inactive, and test state transitions.

adTSUIQIntT1SignalLossEvent.name: adTSUIQIntT1SignalLossEvent
adTSUIQIntT1SignalLossEvent.description: Active state represents one or more signal loss events.

adTSUIQIntT1LoopBackEvent.name: adTSUIQIntT1LoopBackEvent
adTSUIQIntT1LoopBackEvent.description: Active state represents one or more loopback events.

adTSUIQIntT1AISEvent.name: adTSUIQIntT1AISEvent
adTSUIQIntT1AISEvent.description: Active state represents one or more AIS events. AIS is triggered by unframed all ones condition from the T1 service provider.

adTSUIQIntT1RedAlarmEvent.name: adTSUIQIntT1RedAlarmEvent
adTSUIQIntT1RedAlarmEvent.description: Active state represents one or more red alarm events. Red alarm is triggered by loss of frame alignment on the receive T1 signal.

adTSUIQIntT1YellowAlarmEvent.name: adTSUIQIntT1YellowAlarmEvent
adTSUIQIntT1YellowAlarmEvent.description: Active state represents one or more yellow alarm events. Yellow alarm is an indication the service provider has lost frame alignmnet.

adTSUIQIntT1PLLAlarmEvent.name: adTSUIQIntT1PLLAlarmEvent
adTSUIQIntT1PLLAlarmEvent.description: Active state represents one or more PLL alarm events. PLL alarm is an indication that the transmit and receive side of the T1 interface are not looped timed. This will occur when both ends of the T1 are set to provide timing.

adTSUIQIntT1PathCodeViolation.name: adTSUIQIntT1PathCodeViolation
adTSUIQIntT1PathCodeViolation.description: Count of path code violations received. Path code violations are a errors in the frame bit postions for D4 and ESF CRC errors when set for ESF.

adTSUIQIntT1LineCodeViolation.name: adTSUIQIntT1LineCodeViolation
adTSUIQIntT1LineCodeViolation.description: Count of line code violations received. Line code violations are a combination of BPVs that are not part of B8ZS code and excess zeros. Excess zeros are 8 or more consecutive zeros when set for B8ZS and 15 or more consecutive zeros when set for AMI.

adTSUIQDayT1UnavailableTime.name: adTSUIQDayT1UnavailableTime
adTSUIQDayT1UnavailableTime.description: Amount of time in seconds the T1 port is unavailable due to test or in an inactive state.

adTSUIQDayT1StateChange.name: adTSUIQDayT1StateChange
adTSUIQDayT1StateChange.description: Number of changes in the T1 port state. This includes all normal, inactive, and test state transitions.

adTSUIQDayT1SignalLossEvent.name: adTSUIQDayT1SignalLossEvent
adTSUIQDayT1SignalLossEvent.description: Active state represents one or more signal loss events.

adTSUIQDayT1LoopBackEvent.name: adTSUIQDayT1LoopBackEvent
adTSUIQDayT1LoopBackEvent.description: Active state represents one or more loopback events.

adTSUIQDayT1AISEvent.name: adTSUIQDayT1AISEvent
adTSUIQDayT1AISEvent.description: Active state represents one or more AIS events. AIS is triggered by unframed all ones condition from the T1 service provider.

adTSUIQDayT1RedAlarmEvent.name: adTSUIQDayT1RedAlarmEvent
adTSUIQDayT1RedAlarmEvent.description: Active state represents one or more red alarm events. Red alarm is triggered by loss of frame alignment on the receive T1 signal.

adTSUIQDayT1YellowAlarmEvent.name: adTSUIQDayT1YellowAlarmEvent
adTSUIQDayT1YellowAlarmEvent.description: Active state represents one or more yellow alarm events. Yellow alarm is an indication the service provider has lost frame alignmnet.

adTSUIQDayT1PLLAlarmEvent.name: adTSUIQDayT1PLLAlarmEvent
adTSUIQDayT1PLLAlarmEvent.description: Active state represents one or more PLL alarm events. PLL alarm is an indication that the transmit and receive side of the T1 interface are not looped timed. This will occur when both ends of the T1 are set to provide timing.

adTSUIQDayT1PathCodeViolation.name: adTSUIQDayT1PathCodeViolation
adTSUIQDayT1PathCodeViolation.description: Count of path code violations received. Path code violations are a errors in the frame bit postions for D4 and ESF CRC errors when set for ESF.

adTSUIQDayT1LineCodeViolation.name: adTSUIQDayT1LineCodeViolation
adTSUIQDayT1LineCodeViolation.description: Count of line code violations received. Line code violations are a combination of BPVs that are not part of B8ZS code and excess zeros. Excess zeros are 8 or more consecutive zeros when set for B8ZS and 15 or more consecutive zeros when set for AMI.

adTSUIQDiagnosticDlci.name: adTSUIQDiagnosticDlci
adTSUIQDiagnosticDlci.description: Sets the DLCI for PVC Loopback. (Range 16 - 1007).

adTSUIQDiagnosticControl.name: adTSUIQDiagnosticControl
adTSUIQDiagnosticControl.description: Starts or Stops the PVC Loopback Test.

adTSUIQDiagnosticSecondsRemaining.name: adTSUIQDiagnosticSecondsRemaining
adTSUIQDiagnosticSecondsRemaining.description: PVC Loopback Test time remaining in seconds.

adTSUIQ1406TimeStamp.name: adTSUIQ1406TimeStamp
adTSUIQ1406TimeStamp.description: Time interval started. Format H:M if not midnight else M-D

adTSUIQDBUOption.name: adTSUIQDBUOption
adTSUIQDBUOption.description: This option specifies whether the unit automatically enters dial backup mode or waits for manual setup.

adTSUIQDBUStartLockout.name: adTSUIQDBUStartLockout
adTSUIQDBUStartLockout.description: This option selects the hour to begin disabling dial backup operation when daily or weekend lockout mode is active.

adTSUIQDBUEndLockout.name: adTSUIQDBUEndLockout
adTSUIQDBUEndLockout.description: This option selects the hour to end dial backup lockout when daily or weekend lockout mode is active.

adTSUIQDBUMode.name: adTSUIQDBUMode
adTSUIQDBUMode.description: This option specifies the dial backup operating mode for the unit as orginate or answer. One end must be set to originate and the other end to answer.

adTSUIQDBUWithNetworkFailure.name: adTSUIQDBUWithNetworkFailure
adTSUIQDBUWithNetworkFailure.description: This option enables the unit to enter backup mode when T1 network failure occurs.

adTSUIQDBUNoLMI.name: adTSUIQDBUNoLMI
adTSUIQDBUNoLMI.description: This option enables the unit to enter backup mode when network PVC signaling state goes down.

adTSUIQAutoRestoreTimer.name: adTSUIQAutoRestoreTimer
adTSUIQAutoRestoreTimer.description: This option selects the amount of time that the TSUIQ circuit must be active before the unit switches from backup to normal mode of operation. The timer value is in minutes from 0 to 60. A zero value disables automatic restore, TSUIQ operation must be restored manually.

adTSUIQRedialCount.name: adTSUIQRedialCount
adTSUIQRedialCount.description: This option allows the selection of the number of times the unit will redial the Far End unit when attempting to go to backup and a busy or reorder condition occurs. Redial count can be set for a maximum of 60.

adTSUIQDBUFailTimeout.name: adTSUIQDBUFailTimeout
adTSUIQDBUFailTimeout.description: This option allows the selection of the amount of time that the dedicated circuit failure condition is active before attempting to enter dial backup mode. The Fail Timeout value is in increments of 10 seconds up to a maximum of 600 seconds.

adTSUIQDBURedialTimer.name: adTSUIQDBURedialTimer
adTSUIQDBURedialTimer.description: This option works in conjunction with the Redial Counter option. The Redial Timer specifies the amount of time between redial attempts. The Redial Timer value is seconds, up to a maximum of 60 seconds.

adTSUIQDBUPassCheck.name: adTSUIQDBUPassCheck
adTSUIQDBUPassCheck.description: This option allows the unit to send and verify a dial backup passcode for an additional level of security. When enabled, the originate unit sends the passcode and the answer unit checks the passcode before the backup connection is considered valid.

adTSUIQDBUPassCode.name: adTSUIQDBUPassCode
adTSUIQDBUPassCode.description: This option sets the dial backup passcode used to provide an additional level of security. A passcode of one to ten digit characters can be set. If enabled, the originate unit sends the passcode and the answer unit checks the passcode to verify the connection.

adTSUIQWeekendLockout.name: adTSUIQWeekendLockout
adTSUIQWeekendLockout.description: This option enables or disables Weekend Lockout for Dial Backup operation. If enabled, no backup will occur from midnight Friday to midnight Sunday.

adTSUIQDailyLockout.name: adTSUIQDailyLockout
adTSUIQDailyLockout.description: This option enables or disables Daily Lockout for Dial Backup operation. If enabled, no backup will occur between Lockout Start hour and Lockout End hour.

adTSUIQAnswerAlways.name: adTSUIQAnswerAlways
adTSUIQAnswerAlways.description: This option enables or disables Answer Always for Dial Backup operation. If enabled, the answer unit answers any incoming call regardless of failed conditions.

adTSUIQBeeperOption.name: adTSUIQBeeperOption
adTSUIQBeeperOption.description: This option enables or disables the audible alarm when the IQ unit goes into dial backup mode.

adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber1.name: adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber1
adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber1.description: This option is used to set a phone number to place a DBU call.

adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber2.name: adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber2
adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber2.description: This option is used to set a phone number to place a DBU call.

adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber3.name: adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber3
adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber3.description: This option is used to set a phone number to place a DBU call.

adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber4.name: adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber4
adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber4.description: This option is used to set a phone number to place a DBU call.

adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber5.name: adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber5
adTSUIQDBUPhoneNumber5.description: This option is used to set a phone number to place a DBU call.

adTSUIQDBUISDNSwitch.name: adTSUIQDBUISDNSwitch
adTSUIQDBUISDNSwitch.description: This option is used to select the ISDN switch type.

adTSUIQDBUISDNBChannelRate.name: adTSUIQDBUISDNBChannelRate
adTSUIQDBUISDNBChannelRate.description: This option is used to select the ISDN channel rate.

adTSUIQDBUISDNBChannelCount.name: adTSUIQDBUISDNBChannelCount
adTSUIQDBUISDNBChannelCount.description: This option is used to select the number ISDN channels to use.

adTSUIQDBUISDNSPID1.name: adTSUIQDBUISDNSPID1
adTSUIQDBUISDNSPID1.description: This option is used to set the SPID for the ISDN interface.

adTSUIQDBUISDNSPID2.name: adTSUIQDBUISDNSPID2
adTSUIQDBUISDNSPID2.description: This option is used to set the SPID for the ISDN interface.

adTSUIQDBUISDNLDN1.name: adTSUIQDBUISDNLDN1
adTSUIQDBUISDNLDN1.description: This option is used to set LDN for the ISDN interface.

adTSUIQDBUISDNLDN2.name: adTSUIQDBUISDNLDN2
adTSUIQDBUISDNLDN2.description: This option is used to set LDN for the ISDN interface.

adTSUIQV34LineType.name: adTSUIQV34LineType
adTSUIQV34LineType.description: This option selects the type of analog phone line.

adTSUIQDCEInterfaceType.name: adTSUIQDCEInterfaceType
adTSUIQDCEInterfaceType.description: This option enables or disables Answer Always for Dial Backup operation. If enabled, the answer unit answers any incoming call regardless of failed conditions.

adTSUIQDCEBitRate.name: adTSUIQDCEBitRate
adTSUIQDCEBitRate.description: This option is uses for utilization measurement of the DBU port when an external DCE device is used. Set this parameter in KBPS close to the connection rate.

adTSUIQIntDBUFramesRx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUFramesRx
adTSUIQIntDBUFramesRx.description: The number of Frames the Port received for the interval.

adTSUIQIntDBUFramesTx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUFramesTx
adTSUIQIntDBUFramesTx.description: The number of Frames the Port transmitted for the interval.

adTSUIQIntDBUBytesRx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUBytesRx
adTSUIQIntDBUBytesRx.description: The number of Bytes the Port received for the interval.

adTSUIQIntDBUBytesTx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUBytesTx
adTSUIQIntDBUBytesTx.description: The number of Bytes the Port transmitted for the interval.

adTSUIQIntDBUAvgThruputTx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUAvgThruputTx
adTSUIQIntDBUAvgThruputTx.description: The Average Throughput the Port transmitted for the interval.

adTSUIQIntDBUAvgThruputRx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUAvgThruputRx
adTSUIQIntDBUAvgThruputRx.description: The Average Throughput the Port received for the interval.

adTSUIQIntDBUMaxThruputTx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUMaxThruputTx
adTSUIQIntDBUMaxThruputTx.description: The Maximum Throughput the Port transmitted for the interval.

adTSUIQIntDBUMaxThruputRx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUMaxThruputRx
adTSUIQIntDBUMaxThruputRx.description: The Maximum Throughput the Port received for the interval.

adTSUIQIntDBUAvgUtilizationTx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUAvgUtilizationTx
adTSUIQIntDBUAvgUtilizationTx.description: The Average Utilization the Port transmitted for the interval.

adTSUIQIntDBUAvgUtilizationRx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUAvgUtilizationRx
adTSUIQIntDBUAvgUtilizationRx.description: The Average Utilization the Port received for the interval.

adTSUIQIntDBUMaxUtilizationTx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUMaxUtilizationTx
adTSUIQIntDBUMaxUtilizationTx.description: The Maximum Utilization the Port transmitted for the interval.

adTSUIQIntDBUMaxUtilizationRx.name: adTSUIQIntDBUMaxUtilizationRx
adTSUIQIntDBUMaxUtilizationRx.description: The Maximum Utilization the Port received for the interval.

adTSUIQIntTimeInDBU.name: adTSUIQIntTimeInDBU
adTSUIQIntTimeInDBU.description: Time in seconds the DBU port was active.

adTSUIQIntDBUCrcErrors.name: adTSUIQIntDBUCrcErrors
adTSUIQIntDBUCrcErrors.description: Number of frames received with CRC errors.

adTSUIQIntDBUAbortFrames.name: adTSUIQIntDBUAbortFrames
adTSUIQIntDBUAbortFrames.description: Number of frames received without proper flag termination.

adTSUIQIntDBUOctectViolations.name: adTSUIQIntDBUOctectViolations
adTSUIQIntDBUOctectViolations.description: Number of frames received with a bit count not divisible by eigth.

adTSUIQIntDBUDiscardFrames.name: adTSUIQIntDBUDiscardFrames
adTSUIQIntDBUDiscardFrames.description: Number of frames discarded by the IQ unit

adTSUIQIntDBULengthErrors.name: adTSUIQIntDBULengthErrors
adTSUIQIntDBULengthErrors.description: Number of frames received that is less than 5 bytes or greater than 4500 bytes.

adTSUIQIntDBUEncapsulationErrors.name: adTSUIQIntDBUEncapsulationErrors
adTSUIQIntDBUEncapsulationErrors.description: Number of frames destined for the IQ IP stack with that does not meet the FRF.3 IA.

adTSUIQIntDBUUnroutable.name: adTSUIQIntDBUUnroutable
adTSUIQIntDBUUnroutable.description: Number of frames received on a management DLCI destined for the IQ unit and have the wrong IP address.

adTSUIQDayDBUFramesRx.name: adTSUIQDayDBUFramesRx
adTSUIQDayDBUFramesRx.description: The number of Frames the Port received for the interval.

adTSUIQDayDBUFramesTx.name: adTSUIQDayDBUFramesTx
adTSUIQDayDBUFramesTx.description: The number of Frames the Port transmitted for the interval.

adTSUIQDayDBUBytesRx.name: adTSUIQDayDBUBytesRx
adTSUIQDayDBUBytesRx.description: The number of Bytes the Port received for the interval.

adTSUIQDayDBUBytesTx.name: adTSUIQDayDBUBytesTx
adTSUIQDayDBUBytesTx.description: The number of Bytes the Port transmitted for the interval.

adTSUIQDayDBUAvgThruputTx.name: adTSUIQDayDBUAvgThruputTx
adTSUIQDayDBUAvgThruputTx.description: The Average Throughput the Port transmitted for the interval.

adTSUIQDayDBUAvgThruputRx.name: adTSUIQDayDBUAvgThruputRx
adTSUIQDayDBUAvgThruputRx.description: The Average Throughput the Port received for the interval.
